25|$|Barbour {{has been}} accused by Bloomberg News of {{personally}} profiting from Hurricane Katrina recovery. Barbour is an owner of {{the parent company of}} lobbying firm Barbour Griffith & Rogers Inc., and he receives a pension and profit-sharing plan benefits from it. The lobbying firm has lobbied the state to give recovery contracts to its clients. Some of the proceeds of the firm's lobbying activities are deposited into Barbour's investment account. According to Barbour's attorney, a <b>blind</b> <b>trust</b> executed in 2004 prevents Barbour knowing the composition of his investments in order to eliminate any conflicts of interest.|$|E
